main event: An unidentified object with flashing red, green, and white lights was observed in the sky over Wichita Falls, Texas on March 31, 1966.
interesting points: The object made a hissing sound similar to a jet engine, and a contrail was observed as it approached from the east.
The object appeared to move in an east-west holding pattern, similar to the movements of an aircraft over a navigational aid.
Multiple witnesses, including a civilian and two Air Force sergeants, observed the object for approximately 15-60 minutes.
The object was estimated to be around 10 miles away from the observers.
No aircraft were reported in the area at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: an unidentified object with flashing lights
witnesses: a civilian, two Air Force sergeants
